    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-04-13T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-04-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="212"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d212">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.003/3–1942</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Chief of the Division of Far Eastern
                        Affairs</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hamilton</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Under Secretary of State</hi> (<persName
                        type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Welles</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="11" xml:id="d212fn1">The original of this memorandum,
                        attached to the memorandum by Mr. Adams dated March 19, <hi rend="italic"
                            >ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_268">p. 268</ref>, bears the notation “O.
                        K. SW”.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-04-13">April 13,
                            1942</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>You may care to glance at this file.</p>
                <p>Unless you perceive objection, FE<note n="11a" xml:id="d212fn2">Division of Far
                        Eastern Affairs.</note> will take up with TA<note n="12" xml:id="d212fn3"
                        >Division of Commercial Treaties and Agreements.</note> the question of
                    setting up a small committee along the lines indicated in the second paragraph
                    of Mr. Hornbeck’s memorandum of April 9.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>M[<hi rend="smallcaps">axwell</hi>] M. H[<hi rend="smallcaps"
                            >amilton</hi>]</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
